        <worksheet margin="1in" bottom="1.25cm" xml:id="ws-4-2-3">
            <title>Exponential Graphs</title>
            
            <introduction>
                <p>
                     Below we'll practice graphing the family of exponential relationships <m>f(x) = a\cdot b^x + c</m>. 
                     Use the sliders for each parameter to change the graph to a new exponential relationship that goes 
                     through all three points given. 
                </p>
            </introduction>

            <interactive label="ch4-interactive-exp-graph" platform="doenetml" width="100%" aspect="1:1.75">
                <slate surface="doenetml">
                    <xi:include parse="text" href="doenet/ch4-doenet-exp-graph.doenetml"/>
                </slate>
            </interactive>

            <exercise>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                    Choose new variations of the problem with the <q>New Variation</q> 
                     button. Before moving on, attempt at least <m>3</m> different versions, and write down observations 
                     for how graphs of exponential relationships can behave as if you were explaining it to someone new.
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </exercise>

        </worksheet>

